25/01/24, 6:10â€¯pm - ANEKANT JAIN: Some pre-requisites for the tasks: 

1) Members must know about MOU (Memorandum of Understanding) it will help them in NEC finals. It enables you to increase trust and reduce misunderstandings between the parties. There is a link attached below as a reference for learning.
	Link for reference: 
	https://www.investopedia.com/terms/m/mou.asp
2) We are also sharing some links on Entrepreneurship. As we aim to set up an Entrepreneurship Cell, it is highly encouraged to have a basic knowledge of the same. It allows you to think more rationally and consider relevant and feasible initiatives.
	Link for the same:
	https://www.investopedia.com/terms/e/entrepreneur.asp
	https://www.viima.com/blog/idea-validation
	https://www.investopedia.com/terms/b/businessmodel.asp
	https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business_Model_Canvas
	https://inc42.com/resources/what-are-the-different-stages-of-a-startup/
	https://www.cemexventures.com/startup-stages-phases/
25/01/24, 6:10â€¯pm - ANEKANT JAIN: Phases of entrepreneurship:

-idea generation

-opportunity evaluation (Investment prospectus)
Need / problem
Solution
Competitive position
Team (required )
Risk / reward profile

-planning
1. Strategy
 Target customer
Business model(The business model is your theory about how you will make money)
Position
Milestones / company objectives
2. Operating plan
Company timeline(This is a representation of all the major accomplishments or deliverables that are necessary for you to achieve your strategy.)
Staffing plan
Budget
Financing plan

-company formation

-launch and growth
Market research
Marketing
Business development
Forecasting
Sales planning
R&D management
Operations management
People management
Process and infrastructure
Budgeting
Financing





6 P's of entrepreneurship:
Product, people, place, price, presentation, promotion

5 C's of entrepreneurship
Credibility, conviction, clarity, capital, concentration 





Pitch deck  (Process)

-Storylining(Problem,solution)
-Product Research(product features, market fit)
-Competitors analysis 
-Industry Analysis 
-USP analysis
Your USP (Unique Selling Proposition) is the unique thing that you can offer that your competitors can't.
-SWOT analysis
(Strength, weakness, opportunities, threats)
-Traction till date (revenue generated till date)
-Our team
-Financial Modeling 
-Growth potential
-Financial vision
-Investment amount

Keypoints :
Low fidelity slides
Fix design system
Typography
Analysis of financial data

P- Problem solver (Show how you have a solution that works) ...
I- Inspire an action (Have an end goal in mind that you're leading them to) ...
T- Tailor it to the audience. ...
C- Concise (be quick and to the point) ...
H- Heart (Be passionate!)



Strategic marketing
Content marketing
Price elasticity 
Color theory imp acc to product type
Bootstrap - Early stage of startup
Stages of startup
Top down
Bottom up approach
Service available market
GMV
TAM -
   Top down
   bottom up
Break even condition
CAC
LTV
